    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> For example a ValueError is raised when you pass a non formatting string\n> not in front of the %e argument.\n\nNot quite sure what this mean, too many negation. \n\nAnything you pass to %precision will be use a string formatter:\n\n```\nIn [1]: %precision %%c [ %012.7f ] %%$\nOut[1]: '%%c [ %012.7f ] %%$'\n\nIn [2]: 127/9\nOut[2]: %c [ 0014.1111111 ] %$\n```\n\nWe 'just' pass the string you give to `%precision` to a formatter (after checking that it can actually format one number).\n\nI'm not quite sure why we should raise on some formatting string that are valid. \n"
